  <div class="individuals">
    <section class="coaching">
      <div class="title">
        <h2>Selected Projects​</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="contents">
        <div class="content">
          <img src="../public/icons/handshake.svg" alt="Interview coaching icon" />
          <h3>Project</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>The Science of Success​</li>
            <li>Creating the Culture We Want​</li>
            <li>Fractional HR Support​</li>
            <li>Succession Planning Strategy​</li>
            <li>Mindset Drives Behaviour​</li>
            <li>CEO Succession plan​</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="content">
          <img src="../public/icons/user.svg" alt="One-to-one coaching icon" />
          <h3>Focus</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Keynote</li>
            <li>Organisation-wide values launch​</li>
            <li>Organisation Design & Performance​</li>
            <li>Executive Work​</li>
            <li>Team Performance​</li>
            <li>Process, recruitment, leadership training and development, partnering with the new CEO​</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>

  <section class="reset">
    <h3>Reset the Rhythm of Your Organisation</h3>
    <h4>Align leadership, strategy and performance to move forward with clarity and consistency.</h4>
    <p>
      When leadership, behaviour and systems fall out of step, performance slows. This work helps organisations regain
      alignment and momentum.
    </p>
    <div class="btn-section">
      <a
        class="btn-third"
        data-cal-link="stephbe/exec-coaching-clients"
        data-cal-namespace="exec-coaching-clients"
        data-cal-config='{"layout":"month_view"}'>Book a Clarity Conversation</a
      >
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="rhythm-section container">
    <div class="rhythms">
      <div class="rhythm">
        <h4>When Organisations Bring Me In</h4>
        <p>
          Organisations rarely struggle because people don’t care. They struggle because expectations, leadership and
          systems have fallen out of step.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Our strategy is clear, but execution feels inconsistent</li>
          <li>We have strong people, but leadership behaviours aren’t aligned</li>
          <li>Decisions are slower than they should be</li>
          <li>Standards exist, but they aren’t consistently lived</li>
          <li>We’re growing fast and leadership needs to evolve</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          These moments are rarely about capability alone they’re about clarity and alignment. That’s where our work
          begins.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="rhythm">
        <h4>Clarity Changes the Rhythm</h4>
        <p>
          When organisations fall out of step, the instinct is often to add more more processes, more meetings, more
          pressure. Sustainable performance rarely comes from adding more. It comes from clarity.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Clarity about leadership expectations</li>
          <li>Clarity about decision-making</li>
          <li>Clarity about how strategy shows up in behaviour every day</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          This work helps leaders cut through complexity so that people, systems and strategy begin to move together
          again.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="rhythm">
        <h4>The Clarity Series</h4>
        <p>
          A structured leadership framework designed to reduce organisational fog and strengthen trust, alignment and
          performance. Grounded in neuroscience, leadership application and practical tools that translate learning into
          action.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Leadership workshops</li>
          <li>Strategic leadership series</li>
          <li>Keynote presentations</li>
          <li>Custom programmes for organisations</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Each session is designed to create practical shifts in how leaders think, decide and lead.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="content">
      <h2>Ready to Reset the Rhythm?</h2>
      <p>
        If something in your organisation feels out of step whether in leadership, behaviour or execution it’s time to
        create clarity.
      </p>
      <div class="btn-section">
        <a
          class="btn"
          data-cal-link="stephbe/exec-coaching-clients"
          data-cal-namespace="exec-coaching-clients"
          data-cal-config='{"layout":"month_view"}'>Book a Clarity Conversation</a
        >
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="my-story org">
    <section class="about-me">
      <div class="content">
        <div class="text">
          <h3>Speaking & Events that inspire change.​</h3>
          <p>Whether I'm speaking to 30 or 500, my aim is always the same​</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Shift thinking</li>
            <li>Create energy</li>
            <li>Give people practical tools they actually use on Monday morning</li>
          </ul>

          <h4>The Science of Success</h4>
          <p>
            I created an engaging keynote for women in business that went far beyond motivation and gave attendees
            practical, neuroscience-backed tools they could immediately apply to confidence, decision-making and
            success.​ Using stories, audience interaction and accessible neuroscience, I explored how mindset shapes
            behaviour and performance. Rather than simply inspiring the audience, the session focused on creating
            lasting behavioural change through practical tools participants could use in both their businesses and
            personal lives.​ The keynote received outstanding feedback, with delegates describing it as energetic,
            thought-provoking and immediately applicable. Many highlighted that they left with practical strategies they
            could implement straight away, while organisers praised the balance of science, humour and real-world
            relevance.
          </p>
          <span
            >"One of the highest-rated sessions of the event, with delegates continuing the conversation long after the
            keynote had finished."</span
          >

          <h4>Creating the Culture We Want, One Moment at a Time</h4>
          <p>
            I Supported the launch of a new organisational values framework in a way that felt authentic, engaging and
            meaningful for every employee. The aim wasn't simply to explain the values, but to help people understand
            the role they each play in shaping organisational culture.​ Through storytelling, neuroscience and practical
            reflection, the keynote connected individual behaviour to organisational culture using the central message
            that every interaction is a vote for the culture we create. Rather than presenting values as posters on a
            wall, the session invited people to see culture as something built through everyday choices.​ The keynote
            created energy and ownership around the new values, helping employees understand how they could personally
            contribute to the organisation's future culture. Leaders described the session as a strong foundation for
            embedding the values beyond the launch event.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="img">
        <img src="../public/img/my-story/my-story.JPG" alt="Portrait of StephBe in professional setting" />
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</Layout>
